<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Amilya Kalfoxx</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-12 12:47:21</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Babbin's is a fairly random Spawn.  I've been camping Befallen for almost a month now on Prexus and he will turn up more often than the BBC holder and the Theurmalagist Holder.<BR>
At lvl 30 he cons green to yellow, depening on his spawn lvl.  If you manage to catch him right away before he gets his pet up, he's a fairly simple mob.  I managed to wrath him twice for roughly 250 damage and he started to run.  One time when he was green he gave me exp.<BR>
Way to find him, if you have all three keys, use the doors.  Go into the room where the Elf Skellys spawn, down the hall till you come to a door.  Go inside, go over the rubble, go across the hall(straight) through the door, and over the pillar.  Babbin won't attack you even if you're medding on him.  At least he didn't attack me when I was medding on him.<BR>
For the 2nd part of the quest you have to go to EverFrost, Evil races beware, go to the river and take a swim, I recomand enduring breath from an enchanter or druid.  I can't remember exact loc, but look for a bag in a cave.  If I remember correctly there is a bear in there, if you get lucky and I did the couple times I've done this, he was already dead by the time I got there.<BR>
Scrap up 100 to 130 pp's for a plat bar and possibly another 100 to get a high lvl enchanter to enchant the bar and take it back to the Temple of Soluesk.  Talk to the people till you find the one that will galvinze the bar, and have fun.<BR>
Turn them in, and get the glove.  Sadly if you start the quest you must finish it, but the gloves can be given away to other clerics(which is what I do btw).<BR>
<BR>
I hope I help all you clerics out there.<BR>
<BR>
Coming at you from Amilya Kalfoxx of the Prexus Server Alliance of the Blade</font></td></tr></table>
